~ start

if GameState.player.has_ability(256)
	Noria NeedleNest: (lets out a little chuckle) Leaving so soon, little knot? [wave amp=25 freq=5]Hee, hee.[/wave]
	Noria NeedleNest: I'll tell you a secret: the loom never closes all the way. Where the threads are thickest... there's always a gap for those who know how to look.
	Noria NeedleNest: Go on, nose around between them. I'll keep weaving.
	=> END

Noria NeedleNest: Ah. I wove you just this morning, you know? You're a fresh knot in my sock. Right... here.
Noria NeedleNest: Far, far from here, beyond a sea of stolen dreams, there's a flower being erased from the world because almost no one remembers it anymore.
Noria NeedleNest: Someone has to remember it for her. And wouldn't you know it — that someone is you.
Noria NeedleNest: Take that thing there, beside me: a carved snail shell. Blow into it near the sleeping stones and they'll remember they exist... just for a little while.
Noria NeedleNest: Oh, and don't be startled if your thread reaches farther than you expect. I lengthened it while you slept. You're going to need it.
=> END
